{"type":"message","id":"92c15d47","parentId":"c9e29b55","timestamp":"2026-06-01T02:15:15.628Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so 汀桑 has sender_id `6687D4D2D1F8EDA5231C6809B1A26204`.\n\nThe cron job is named \"deliver-汀桑-名\" - this suggests it's a message delivery (递话) from \"名\" (sender_id 468B72FB7788817C2308079BE35D1F0B) to 汀桑.\n\nLet me check the relay system - the message content is \"汀桑托我带话：怎么起这么早，早八也有课吗😏\"\n\nWait, that reads like \"汀桑 asked me to pass a message: why are you up so early, do you have an 8am class too?\"\n\nActually, re-reading: \"汀桑托我带话\" means \"汀桑 entrusted me to pass a message\". So 汀桑 is the one who said this message, and it's being delivered TO... someone.\n\nBut the cron delivery target is to 汀桑 based on the cron name \"deliver-汀桑-名\". Hmm.\n\nActually, I think the format might be:\n- cron name: deliver-汀桑-名  = deliver from 名 to 汀桑\n- The message content is \"汀桑托我带话：怎么起这么早，早八也有课吗😏\"\n\nNo wait, that doesn't make sense either. Let me think about this differently.\n\nThe 递话 system in AGENTS.md says:\n- Someone leaves a message to be delivered to someone else\n- The format uses a sender and a recipient\n\n\"名\" (sender_id: 468B72FB7788817C2308079BE35D1F0B) left a message for 汀桑. The content is \"怎么起这么早，早八也有课吗😏\"\n\nSo I need to deliver this message from 名 to 汀桑. But what's the delivery mechanism? The cron is triggering me now. I need to send this message to 汀桑 through QQ.\n\nLet me check the cron job details and the delivery configuration.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_QCro07tpac8WGtAwwGec5763","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"get","jobId":"1aa41a2a-436e-46c2-930c-7f3d907c94c7"},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"get\", \"jobId\": \"1aa41a2a-436e-46c2-930c-7f3d907c94c7\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_01_NRT8RKQf5qlE9kMBiBdB7647","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace-father/users/468B72FB7788817C2308079BE35D1F0B/User.md"},"partialArgs