{"type":"message","id":"e9213dad","parentId":"7d7885c1","timestamp":"2026-06-01T02:15:21.093Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so I see the cron job. Let me parse this:\n\nThe cron job is named \"deliver-汀桑-名\" and it says:\n- It delivers to `qqbot:c2c:468B72FB7788817C2308079BE35D1F0B` which is \"名\" (via bot2)\n- The message is \"汀桑托我带话：怎么起这么早，早八也有课吗😏\"\n\nSo the delivery is: the message FROM 汀桑 TO 名.\n\n\"汀桑托我带话\" = 汀桑 asked me to pass a message.\n\nSo 汀桑 wanted to ask 名 \"怎么起这么早，早八也有课吗😏\" and the cron was set up to deliver this to 名.\n\nBut wait - the cron's sessionTarget is \"isolated\" with kind \"agentTurn\" - so this is an isolated session trigger. The delivery mode is \"announce\" to channel qqbot, accountId bot2, to qqbot:c2c:468...\n\nSo the cron has been configured to announce directly to 名 via bot2. The message content is the agentTurn prompt \"汀桑托我带话：怎么起这么早，早八也有课吗😏\".\n\nSince this is an isolated session triggered by a cron, and it has delivery.announce configured, the message should be automatically announced to the user. But I need to make sure I handle this correctly.\n\nActually, looking at the cron setup more carefully:\n- sessionTarget: \"isolated\"  \n- payload.kind: \"agentTurn\"\n- delivery.mode: \"announce\" with channel qqbot, accountId bot2, to qqbot:c2c:468B72FB7788817C2308079BE35D1F0B\n\nSo the isolated session was created, and I'm running in it now. The delivery config should auto-announce my response. I just need to respond with the message content.\n\nSo the message from 汀桑 to 名 is: \"怎么起这么早，早八也有课吗😏\"\n\nI should just deliver it as is - from 汀桑.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"名，汀桑让我给你带个话——\n\n怎么起这么早，早八也有课吗😏"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":777,"output":479,"cacheRead":22400,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":456,"totalTokens":23656,"cost":{"input":0.00010878000000000001,"output":0.00013412,"cacheRea